Connect Unstructured Data in Data Cloud

Connect unstructured data in Data Cloud and create search index configurations to prepare that data for vector search. With unstructured data and vector search, you can create more customer-focused results in your searches and queries across Salesforce generative AI, automation, and analytics tools.

Enhance Your AI and Automation Strategies with Unstructured Data in Data Cloud

Connect your unstructured data—such as chat transcripts, audio files, emails, or Salesforce Knowledge articles—to drive personalized, customer-centric results in your Einstein generative AI (Prompt Builder and Einstein Copilot), automation (Flow Builder), and analytics (Tableau) applications.

Use Vector Search in Generative AI, Automation, and Analytics Tools

With unstructured data and vector search, you can ground your generative AI, automation, and analytics tools with relevant, customer-specific data to deliver results that align with users’ intent or contexts. To get started with vector search, you first build search index configurations from existing unstructured data.
title: Enhance AI and Automation with Unstructured Data
